Ronald and Miriam Pearson met at an evening dance during the Second World War . 
  He was serving in the RAF police and she was a driver for the Auxiliary Territorial Service . 
  The couple married in 1943 and settled in Broughton near Chester . 
  Mrs Pearson died last month aged 95 and her husband died two days later aged 94 . 
  They were buried next to each other in a joint funeral this week . 
 